getYWellName

public java.lang.String getYWellName()
Returns the name of a well in the y-direction. The well with the wellY value of 0 corresponds to "A", with 1 to "B", and so on. After the name "Z", the next well is named "AA", then "AB", and so on.

Returns:
Name of y-position of the well.

getYWellName

public static java.lang.String getYWellName(int wellY)
Returns the name of a well in the y-direction. The well with the wellY value of 0 corresponds to "A", with 1 to "B", and so on. After the name "Z", the next well is named "AA", then "AB", and so on.

Parameters:
wellY - The y-position of the well, starting at 0.
Returns:
Name of y-position of the well.

getWellName

public java.lang.String getWellName()
Returns the common name for a well, e.g. "B3" for the well with wellY=1 and wellX=4 (remark: internally, the numbering of the wells starts with 0.). Same as getYWellName() + getXWellName().

Returns:
Common name of the well.

getWellName

public static java.lang.String getWellName(int wellY,
                                           int wellX)
Returns the common name for a well, e.g. "B3" for the well with wellY=1 and wellX=4 (remark: internally, the numbering of the wells starts with 0.). Same as getYWellName(wellY) + getXWellName(wellX).

Parameters:
wellY - The y-position of the well, starting at 0.
wellX - The x-position of the well, starting at 0.
Returns:
Common name of the well.
